  "body": "Distributed Validators Require Signed Contents To Be The Same - ValidatorRegistrationV1\r\n\r\nThe current implementation of the validator registration isn't compatible with a distributed validator\r\n\r\nFor distributed validators it's important that the signed contents are the same across all \"co-validators\"\r\n\r\nthe \"pubkey: BLSPubkey\" included in the message will be the \"pubshare\" not the \"group/root pubkey\" since each co-validator in a distributed validator only knows about its pubshare not about the group pubkey.\r\n\r\nAgain the simplest implementation is likely to have another --X param for  \"registration pubkey override\" and then the DVT validators will have to coordinate and make sure that the flag is set correctly across all co-validators",
